description:
Featuring Johnny Ball... And see more about the egg formula at https://youtu.be/tjyFw1BX4eM
More links about Johnny & stuff in full description below ↓↓↓

Johnny Ball website (with links to shows and other info): https://johnnyball.co.uk
Johnny Ball books on Amazon: https://amzn.to/3uMxB67
More Johnny Ball on Numberphile: https://bit.ly/Johnny_Ball

See the extra video with Val Narushin on the egg equation at https://youtu.be/tjyFw1BX4eM
The paper (Egg and math: introducing a universal formula for egg shape) is officially at:  https://nyaspubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/nyas.14680 (may require a subscription or payment)
A free preprint (not the published version but similar) is at: https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.08.15.252148v1.full 

The Super Egg on Numberphile: https://youtu.be/GznQgTdEdI4

Numberphile is supported by the Mathematical Sciences Research Institute (MSRI): http://bit.ly/MSRINumberphile

We are also supported by Science Sandbox, a Simons Foundation initiative dedicated to engaging everyone with the process of science. https://www.simonsfoundation.org/outreach/science-sandbox/

And support from The Akamai Foundation - dedicated to encouraging the next generation of technology innovators and equitable access to STEM education - https://www.akamai.com/company/corporate-responsibility/akamai-foundation
